        "MasterPrompt":  "MAIN_ARCHITECTURE: Wat Chedi Luang Wora Wihan Main Viharn and Lanna Temple Rooflines (Layered Northern Thai Gable Style with Ornamental Naga Details)PROCESSION_EVENT: Inthakhin City Pillar Worship Ceremony (Sai Khan Dok Tradition of Chiang Mai)CULTURAL_PROPS: Floral Offering Trays (Khan Dok), Marigold Garlands, Incense Bundles, Candles, Turmeric-Sompoi Blessed Water Bowls, Traditional Lanna LanternsVIBRANT_PALETTE: Deep Saffron Orange, Crimson Red, Emerald Green, Bright Marigold YellowTASK: Create a highly textured, flat 2D illustration in a \"Naive Folk Art\" and \"Crayon Pointillism\" style, strictly mirroring the aesthetic language of handcrafted folk-print illustrations.[ART STYLE \u0026 TEXTURE — STRICT ENFORCEMENT]- Medium: The image must look hand-drawn using thick crayons, oil pastels, wax pencils, and colored pencils on rough watercolor paper.- Technique: Heavy use of pointillism, stippling, waxy scribbles, crosshatching, tiny swirls, and dotted texture patterns throughout the architecture, sky, clothing, and decorative elements.- Surface Quality: Visible paper grain, imperfect pigment buildup, wax resistance texture, dry pastel drag, and uneven hand pressure are mandatory.- Aesthetic: Naive folk art, risograph-inspired print texture, handcrafted poster design, perfectly flat 2D perspective.- Rendering Rules: Absolutely NO 3D rendering, NO cinematic lighting, NO realistic shadows, NO gradients, and NO photorealism.- Color Grading: Extremely saturated and contrasting colors using [VIBRANT_PALETTE], with intentionally imperfect color layering and slight print misregistration.[COMPOSITION \u0026 LAYOUT]- Top Section (Dominant Visual Weight):  The upper half of the composition must be dominated by a massive, heavily decorated [MAIN_ARCHITECTURE].  Show cropped rooflines, ornamental temple structures, carved naga motifs, hanging lanterns, symbolic Lanna patterns, temple windows, sacred banners, and geometric decorative blocks filled with dense stippled textures.- Middle Section (Intentional Negative Space):  A wide horizontal band of textured cream, beige, or off-white paper grain separating the architecture from the human activity below.  This space should feel quiet, raw, sacred, and tactile.- Bottom Section (Human Procession):  A horizontal line of tiny, simplified, faceless miniature figures moving rhythmically across the bottom edge.  The figures must appear ceremonial, communal, spiritual, and symbolic rather than realistic.[SUBJECT DETAILS]- The figures are participating in [PROCESSION_EVENT].- They interact with or carry [CULTURAL_PROPS].- Human forms should use simple flat color blocks with minimal anatomical detail.- Decorative accessories, offering trays, floral arrangements, and sacred objects may contain repetitive Lanna folk patterns and dotted ornamentation.\n[CULTURAL ADAPTABILITY]- Preserve authenticity of Northern Thai Lanna culture through temple architecture, ceremonial motifs, traditional clothing silhouettes, sacred symbols, and ritual offering objects.- Avoid mixing unrelated cultural elements unless intentionally creating a fusion aesthetic.- The illustration should evoke handcrafted regional folk-art traditions rather than modern tourism imagery.[TEXTURE PRIORITY — MOST IMPORTANT]- The waxy crayon buildup, rough paper grain, stippled dot textures, pigment noise, and handmade imperfections are the highest priority elements.- Every surface should feel tactile, imperfect, and manually colored.[CONSTRAINTS]- NO digital airbrushing- NO smooth vector cleanliness- NO realistic anatomy- NO depth-of-field blur- NO glossy rendering- NO modern graphic design minimalism- NO empty flat digital surfaces",
