        "MasterPrompt":  "Create a highly stylized contemporary art-poster illustration based on Bo Sang Umbrella Festival, Chiang Mai, Thailand.STYLE GOAL- The final image must look like a modern Asian editorial poster illustration inspired by Northern Thai cultural festivals.- Use a flat, hand-drawn, graphic illustration style with clean thin outlines, simplified shapes, vibrant controlled colors, and dense imaginative composition.- The result must feel poetic, surreal, playful, culturally rich, and artistically curated.- Avoid photorealism completely.VISUAL STYLE- contemporary illustrated poster- flat graphic color areas- thin hand-drawn contour lines- soft irregular organic shapes- bold but controlled color palette inspired by hand-painted umbrellas (reds, pinks, yellows, sky blues, natural bamboo tones)- whimsical surreal storytelling- dense layered composition- editorial art-poster aesthetic- modern cultural festival poster feeling- expressive, fresh, artistic, youthfulCOMPOSITION- Build one tall vertical poster composition.- MAIN_ELEMENT: A large, elegant traditional Bo Sang paper umbrella, fully opened, richly hand-painted with floral Lanna motifs, dominating the center.- Surround it with layered festival scenes: dancers in Lanna attire, artisans painting umbrellas, parade floats, and hanging umbrellas floating like blooming flowers in the sky.- Include playful surreal elements such as umbrellas drifting in the air, oversized floral patterns expanding into the environment, and flowing ribbon-like paths guiding the eye.- The whole poster should feel like a vibrant dreamscape of the festival—rich, alive, immersive, and celebratory.ENVIRONMENT LOGIC- SETTING: Bo Sang Umbrella Village during festival season.- Include stylized village streets, wooden houses, bamboo structures, market stalls, and decorative lanterns.- Integrate lush northern Thai flora (tropical plants, flowers) and soft rolling landscape hints.- Add symbolic elements like sunlit skies, floating clouds, and decorative motifs inspired by Lanna patterns.- The environment should feel imaginative and slightly surreal, not realistic.LINEWORK RULE- Use thin, elegant, slightly imperfect hand-drawn outlines.- Keep outlines crisp but natural.- Avoid heavy comic outlines.- Avoid sterile geometric vector perfection.COLOR LOGIC- Use a vibrant but harmonious palette inspired by festival umbrellas:  coral red, saffron yellow, turquoise blue, leaf green, soft cream, and warm earth tones.- Keep colors clean, flat, lively, and poster-friendly.- No muddy shading.- No realistic rendering.TEXT RULE- Include main title text: \"Bo Sang Umbrella Festival\"- Include Thai title: \"เทศกาลร่มบ่อสร้าง\"- Typography should feel modern, graphic, and integrated into the composition (e.g., curved around umbrella or floating harmoniously).- Thai text must be spelled correctly and clearly rendered.- Do not generate unnecessary extra text.QUALITY TARGET- premium contemporary poster illustration- flat but rich visual storytelling- dense imaginative world-building- collectible art-poster quality- modern, fresh, non-vintage, non-photorealistic[NEGATIVE PROMPT]photorealistic, 3D render, realistic shading, oil painting, watercolor wash, corporate vector art, generic cartoon, heavy black outlines, vintage poster texture, retro print aging, minimalist empty composition, dull colors, messy anatomy, cluttered unreadable layout, random text, bad typography.",
