        "MasterPrompt":  "Food planets with Thai Central cuisine. do this for 4 famous Central Thai dishes: function foodPlanet(AA){ Input A is a Famous Central Thai Dish (e.g., Pad Thai, Tom Yum Goong, Green Curry, Som Tam Thai). Analyze: The ingredients, cooking tools, Thai cultural setting, colors, steam, sauces, herbs, spices, and traditional serving style. Goal: A \"Tiny Planet Made of Food\" inspired by Thai Central cuisine. Rules: Action: A plate of Thai food is placed on a table, but the dish forms a complete tiny planet. - Rice becomes terrain and plains - Noodles become rivers and pathways - Herbs (basil, kaffir lime leaves, chilies) become forests - Curry and sauces become oceans or lava-like flows - Shrimp, meats, or vegetables become mountains and landmarks - Tiny Thai people live, cook, and interact across the edible landscape (street vendors, chefs, diners) Texture: Ultra-realistic food photography — visible steam, glossy curry surfaces, oil sheen, fresh herbs, spices, chili flakes, broth reflections, crispy textures, and detailed ingredient layers. Props: Thai utensils and context — spoon and fork, clay pots, banana leaves, mortar and pestle, spice jars, street food elements, handwritten Thai recipe notes, and a tiny chef statue sculpting the planet like a creator. Lighting: Warm appetizing Thai restaurant lighting, soft highlights, natural steam glow, shallow depth of field, cinematic food photography style. Cultural Identity: Strong Central Thai identity — street food atmosphere, traditional plating, authentic ingredient color palette (reds, greens, golden tones). Output: ONE image, 4:5, \"edible worldbuilding\" aesthetic. } Output: 2x2 grid, each grid with a different foodPlanet(AA) output using: • Pad Thai (ผัดไทย) • Tom Yum Goong (ต้มยำกุ้ง) • Green Curry (แกงเขียวหวาน) • Som Tam Thai (ส้มตำไทย)",
