        "MasterPrompt":  "Desserts, but make it peer-reviewed. 🥥🔥🥄  Powered by coconut milk, charcoal heat, and questionable culinary science.Image by Gemini Nano Banana Pro.The prompt 👇A vintage, technical scientific diagram of [GIANT KHANOM KROK — Thai Coconut Pancakes], styled as a 1920s laboratory blueprint mixed with a retro Siamese culinary research document.The central dessert is an enormous, highly detailed tray of traditional Thai khanom krok with crispy golden edges and glossy coconut custard centers, rendered like an engineering prototype under scientific examination.Surround the dessert with elaborate pseudo-scientific callouts using absurdly academic terminology such as:- “Thermally Aerated Coconut Emulsion”- “Rice-Flour Structural Integrity Layer”- “Caramelized Peripheral Crispness Ring”- “Hydrodynamic Pandan Aroma Dispersion”- “Granulated Palm-Sucrose Activation”- “Charcoal Heat Distribution Chamber”Include multiple vintage-style scientific data visualizations such as:- “Coconut Density Calibration Graph”- “Crispness-to-Creaminess Ratio Scale”- “Sweetness Volatility Spectrum”- “Thermal Browning Timeline”- “Texture Hardness Index” inspired by the Mohs mineral scale- “Pandan Aromatic Diffusion Hexagon”- “Optimal Spoon Penetration Diagram”The background should be aged, tea-stained parchment mixed with antique Siamese manuscript aesthetics and Victorian laboratory design.Decorate the composition with:- ornate engraved borders- old botanical coconut sketches- charcoal stove engineering diagrams- handwritten formula annotations- antique thermometers- brass measuring instruments- retro kitchen blueprints- “Registered No. 1923” archival stamp- fictional culinary certification sealsAdd small technical illustrations of:- coconut halves- rice flour containers- pandan leaves- traditional cast-iron khanom krok pans- charcoal embers- miniature scientific cutaway diagrams of the dessert interiorTypography style:old-world scientific engraving typography,Victorian laboratory labels,retro apothecary aesthetics,1920s engineering-manual layout,mixed with subtle vintage Thai signage influence.Aesthetic:Retro-futurism,Da Vinci culinary sketchbook meets antique Thai dessert laboratory,old-school soda shop menu mixed with Victorian food science,absurd academic dessert engineering,warm nostalgic handcrafted atmosphere.Color palette:aged parchment beige,charcoal black,burnt coconut brown,pandan green accents,cream white,oxidized brass,faded ink blue.Mood:ridiculously overanalyzed,scholarly but playful,handcrafted,nostalgic,chaotic culinary science energy,like a forgotten dessert experiment from a Siamese royal food laboratory.Output:ultra-detailed vertical poster,high-resolution print-ready artwork,dense scientific infographic composition,aged paper texture,ornate technical illustration aesthetic,humorous pseudo-academic dessert blueprint masterpiece.",
